725513f-a.title: Queens: 60th Street - Metropolitan Avenue
725513f-a.text:
60th Street (formerly Thocpson also John Street), east side,
south from Eetropolitan Avenue, shown at the S.E. corner a frame
structure known as Reis Hotel in 1904. It was still standing in
1934. At the right background near Bleeker Street is P.S. No. 71.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
